# Formatting & Code Style Rules

## HTML Rules
- Use semantic HTML tags
- Maintain proper heading hierarchy (H1-H3)
- Use meaningful class names
- Avoid unnecessary div nesting

## CSS Rules
- Use reusable CSS classes
- Prefer Flexbox and Grid for layouts
- Avoid inline styles
- Use consistent spacing and naming conventions

## JavaScript Rules
- Keep code beginner friendly
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Avoid unnecessary complexity
- Keep functions small and readable

## Naming Conventions
- Use kebab-case for CSS class names
- Use camelCase for JavaScript variables/functions
- Keep naming descriptive and readable

## General Formatting
- Keep code clean and maintainable
- Avoid duplicate code
- Follow existing project structure
